cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based image compression framework that utilizes semantic segmentation maps. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves encoding and decoding techniques, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of deep learning models for image compression also relates to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed framework in terms of PSNR and MS-SSIM metrics, which are commonly used in image and video compression research, further supporting the inclusion of cs.MM. Finally, the paper's focus on image compression and its use of deep learning models make it less likely to belong to other sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
